This paper deals with object discovery and detection in robotic applications using self-supervision. The paper involves computer vision techniques such as clustering and learning object representations from unlabelled images, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision sub-category (cs.CV). The paper also involves the use of robots to traverse an environment, which suggests that it belongs to the robotics sub-category (cs.RO). The paper involves machine learning techniques such as learning representations and detectors, which suggests that it belongs to the machine learning sub-categories (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques such as clustering, which suggests that it belongs to the natural language processing sub-category (cs.CL).
